<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <p>Scoonie Medical Practice is a data controller under the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018. We are registered with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO).</p>

  <h2>What personal information we hold</h2>
  <p>As part of providing your NHS care, we hold personal and special category (health) data about you, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your name, address, date of birth, and contact details</li>
    <li>Your NHS number and registration details</li>
    <li>Your medical history, diagnoses, and treatment records</li>
    <li>Information about your medications and allergies</li>
    <li>Correspondence from other healthcare providers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your information</h2>
  <p>We use your personal information to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide you with NHS primary care services</li>
    <li>Coordinate your care with other NHS providers</li>
    <li>Send you appointment reminders and health screening invitations</li>
    <li>Comply with our legal and regulatory obligations</li>
    <li>Support NHS planning, research, and public health monitoring (using anonymised data where possible)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal basis for processing</h2>
  <p>We process your personal data on the basis of:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Performance of a public task (providing NHS healthcare)</li>
    <li>Vital interests (emergency care)</li>
    <li>Consent (where applicable, such as for research)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For special category health data, we rely on Article 9(2)(h) UK GDPR — medical purposes and the provision of health or social care.</p>

  <h2>Who we share your information with</h2>
  <p>We may share your information with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>NHS Fife and other NHS Trusts involved in your care</li>
    <li>Specialist hospitals, consultants, and community services</li>
    <li>Pharmacies for prescription management</li>
    <li>Social care services when relevant to your welfare</li>
    <li>NHS Digital and Public Health Scotland for national health monitoring (anonymised or pseudonymised)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your data or share it with commercial organisations for marketing purposes.</p>

  <h2>How long we keep your records</h2>
  <p>We retain your medical records in line with NHS Scotland Records Management guidance. GP records are typically retained for 10 years after a patient's death, or permanently for certain record types.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of your personal data (subject access request)</li>
    <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate information</li>
    <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — in limited circumstances, ask us to delete your data</li>
    <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — ask us to restrict how we process your data</li>
    <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
    <li><strong>Object</strong> — object to certain types of processing</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> or in writing to Cameron Health Centre, Methil, Leven, KY8 3LG.</p>

  <h2>Complaints</h2>
  <p>If you have concerns about how we handle your data, you can contact the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a> or on 0303 123 1113.</p>

  <h2>Contact our Data Protection Officer</h2>
  <p>NHS Fife acts as our data protection officer for primary care purposes. You can contact the NHS Fife DPO at:</p>
